main event: Several objects were observed in Duluth, Minnesota, on February 26, moving irregularly and described as football-shaped with flashing lights.
interesting points: The objects were observed for about 3 to 5 minutes by an investigating officer., The estimated elevation of the objects was 30 degrees and at a distance of 5 to 6 miles., The objects emitted alternating red and green colors., No physical evidence was reported from the sighting., A senior director concluded the object was a star after verification.
